1 (IX) IN REM FORECLOSURE PROCEEDINGS;
2 (X) EASEMENT, OR ANY OTHER INTEREST IN LAND;
3 (XI) LEASE; AND
4 (XII) RENT;
5 (8) ACQUIRE, PURCHASE, HOLD, LEASE AS LESSEE, AND USE:
6 (I) A FRANCHISE, PATENT, OR LICENSE;
7 (II) ANY REAL, PERSONAL, MIXED, TANGIBLE, OR INTANGIBLE
8 PROPERTY; OR
9 (III) AN INTEREST IN THE PROPERTY LISTED IN THIS ITEM;
10 (9) FINANCE ALL OR PART OF THE ACQUISITION OR IMPROVEMENT OF
11 A PROJECT;
12 (10) SELL, LEASE AS LESSOR, TRANSFER, LICENSE, ASSIGN, OR
13 DISPOSE OF PROPERTY OR A PROPERTY INTEREST THAT THE AUTHORITY
14 ACQUIRES;
15 (11) FIX AND COLLECT RATES, RENTALS, FEES, ROYALTIES, AND
16 CHARGES FOR SERVICES AND RESOURCES THE AUTHORITY PROVIDES OR MAKES
17 AVAILABLE;
18 (12) ENTER INTO CONTRACTS WITH ANY FEDERAL, STATE, OR LOCAL
19 GOVERNMENT AGENCY, A GOVERNMENTAL UNIT, A COLLEGE OR UNIVERSITY,
20 CHARITABLE INSTITUTIONS, OR A PRIVATE ENTITY OR PARTY;
21 (13) EXERCISE POWER USUALLY POSSESSED BY A PRIVATE
22 CORPORATION IN PERFORMING SIMILAR FUNCTIONS UNLESS TO DO SO WOULD
23 CONFLICT WITH STATE LAW;
24 (14) WITH THE OWNER’S PERMISSION, ENTER LANDS OR PREMISES TO
25 MAKE A SURVEY, A SOUNDING, A BORING, OR AN EXAMINATION TO ACCOMPLISH THE
26 PURPOSE AUTHORIZED BY THIS SUBTITLE;
27 (15) CREATE, OWN, CONTROL, OR BE A MEMBER OF A CORPORATION,
28 LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY, PARTNERSHIP, OR ANY OTHER ENTITY;

HOUSE BILL 1452 11
1 (16) CREATE A SPECIAL DISTRICT BENEFIT FOR THE COMMERCIAL
2 BUSINESSES IN THE TARGET AREA;
3 (17) OPEN A BANK ACCOUNT WITH A NATIONAL OR LOCAL FEDERALLY
4 INSURED FINANCIAL INSTITUTION;
5 (18) SET SALARIES IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE JURISDICTION MARKET
6 RATE AND OUTSIDE THE STATE PERSONNEL AND PENSION SYSTEM;
7 (19) CREATE A FORUM FOR STAKEHOLDERS TO COME TOGETHER ON
8 CREATING A 20–YEAR COMPREHENSIVE PLAN AROUND ECONOMIC, HOUSING,
9 TRANSPORTATION, NEIGHBORHOOD, AND GREEN SPACE DEVELOPMENT WITHIN
10 THE TARGET AREA;
11 (20) SERVE AS A CLEARINGHOUSE AND RESOURCE CENTER FOR
12 PROMOTING COORDINATION AND COMMUNICATION ON DEVELOPMENT
13 OPPORTUNITIES FOR THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION;
14 (21) ENSURE MONEY IS BEING SPENT EFFECTIVELY AND EFFICIENTLY
15 ON DEVELOPMENT AND THAT DEVELOPMENT IS HAPPENING IN THE APPROPRIATE
16 WAY FOR THE SUITLAND ROAD AND SILVER HILL ROAD INTERSECTION;
17 (22) PROVIDE ADVISORY SERVICES TO STATE AND PRINCE GEORGE’S
18 COUNTY AGENCIES ON PLANNING AND DEVELOPMENT FOR THE TARGET AREA;
19 (23) INITIATE, FUND, AND MONITOR FOR EFFICIENCY AND
20 EFFECTIVENESS ECONOMIC, HOUSING, TRANSPORTATION, NEIGHBORHOOD, AND
21 GREEN SPACE DEVELOPMENT WITHIN THE TARGET AREA;
22 (24) MAKE RULES AND REGULATIONS FOR THE OPERATION AND USE
23 OF LAND, PROPERTY, AND UNDERTAKINGS UNDER THE AUTHORITY’S
24 JURISDICTION; AND
25 (25) DO ALL THINGS NECESSARY OR CONVENIENT TO CARRY OUT THE
26 POWERS EXPRESSLY GRANTED BY THIS SUBTITLE.
27 12–1211.
28 (A) THE AUTHORITY SHALL ESTABLISH A SYSTEM OF FINANCIAL
29 ACCOUNTING, CONTROLS, AUDITS, AND REPORTS.

12 HOUSE BILL 1452
1 (B) THE FISCAL YEAR OF THE AUTHORITY BEGINS ON JULY 1 AND ENDS ON
2 THE FOLLOWING JUNE 30.
3 12–1212.
4 (A) THE AUTHORITY MAY CREATE AND ADMINISTER THE ACCOUNTS THAT
5 THE AUTHORITY REQUIRES.
6 (B) THE AUTHORITY SHALL DEPOSIT ITS MONEY INTO A PRINCE GEORGE’S
7 COUNTY OR NATIONAL BANK OR A FEDERALLY INSURED SAVINGS AND LOAN
8 ASSOCIATION THAT HAS A TOTAL PAID–IN CAPITAL OF AT LEAST $1,000,000.
9 (C) THE AUTHORITY MAY DESIGNATE THE TRUST DEPARTMENT OF A
10 PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY OR NATIONAL BANK OR SAVINGS AND LOAN
11 ASSOCIATION AS A DEPOSITORY TO RECEIVE SECURITIES THAT THE AUTHORITY
12 OWNS OR ACQUIRES.
13 12–1213.
14 (A) EXCEPT AS PROVIDED IN SUBSECTION (B) OF THIS SECTION, THE
15 AUTHORITY IS EXEMPT FROM TAXATION OR ASSESSMENTS ON ANY PART OF A
16 DEVELOPMENT OR PROJECT, THE AUTHORITY’S ACTIVITIES IN OPERATING AND
17 MAINTAINING A DEVELOPMENT OR PROJECT, AND REVENUES FROM A
18 DEVELOPMENT OR PROJECT.
19 (B) ANY PROPERTY THAT IS SOLD OR LEASED BY THE AUTHORITY TO A
20 PRIVATE ENTITY IS SUBJECT TO PRINCE GEORGE’S COUNTY AND LOCAL REAL
21 PROPERTY TAXES FROM THE TIME OF SALE OR LEASE.
22 (C) THE AUTHORITY IS EXEMPT FROM STATE AND LOCAL TRANSFER AND
23 RECORDATION TAX.
24 (D) THE AUTHORITY IS EXEMPT FROM THE SALES AND USE TAX ON
25 CONSTRUCTION MATERIALS FOR A PROJECT IN THE TARGET AREA OF THE BUFFER
26 ZONE.
27 12–1214.
28 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “FUND” MEANS THE SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT
29 AUTHORITY FUND.
30 (B) THERE IS A SUITLAND DEVELOPMENT AUTHORITY FUND.

HOUSE BILL 1452 13
1 (C) THE PURPOSE OF THE FUND IS TO PROVIDE FUNDS FOR THE
2 AUTHORITY TO USE FOR CONSULTING FEES, SALARIES, AND ADMINISTRATIVE
3 EXPENSES.
4 (D) THE AUTHORITY SHALL ADMINISTER THE FUND.
5 (E) (1) THE FUND IS A SPECIAL, NONLAPSING FUND THAT IS NOT
6 SUBJECT TO § 7–302 OF THE STATE FINANCE AND PROCUREMENT ARTICLE.
7 (2) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL HOLD THE FUND SEPARATELY,
8 AND THE COMPTROLLER SHALL ACCOUNT FOR THE FUND.
9 (F) THE FUND CONSISTS OF:
10 (1) MONEY APPROPRIATED IN THE STATE BUDGET TO THE FUND;
11 (2) INTEREST EARNINGS; AND
12 (3) ANY OTHER MONEY FROM ANY OTHER SOURCE ACCEPTED FOR
13 THE BENEFIT OF THE FUND.
14 (G) THE FUND MAY BE USED ONLY FOR ADMINISTRATIVE PURPOSES AND TO
15 CARRY OUT THE FUNCTIONS OF THIS SUBTITLE.
16 (H) THE STATE TREASURER SHALL INVEST THE MONEY OF THE FUND IN
17 THE SAME MANNER AS OTHER STATE MONEY MAY BE INVESTED.
18 (I) EXPENDITURES FROM THE FUND MAY BE MADE ONLY IN ACCORDANCE
19 WITH THE STATE BUDGET.
